tree_model <- rpart(can_off_sta ~., data = camcleandata,
                    method = 'class'
                    , control = rpart.control(minbucket =1, minsplit = 1
                                              , cp=0))

rpart.plot(tree_model)
## Warning: All boxes will be white (the box.palette argument will be ignored) because
## the number of classes in the response 57 is greater than length(box.palette) 6.
## To silence this warning use box.palette=0 or trace=-1.
## Warning: labs do not fit even at cex 0.15, there may be some overplotting

prunemodel <- prune(tree_model, cp=0.02)
rpart.plot(prunemodel)
